<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-13T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-13T11:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/665: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-13T11:00:00-05:00">June 13, 1934—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>319. Department’s 91, June 12, 5 p.m. Cuban delegates state that a few
                            final requests for concessions (largely minor ones) will be delivered to
                            us tomorrow.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>